---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const keywords = [
  'Endomidface fixation vectors',
  'vertical vector facelift',
  'midface fixation technique',
  'deep temporal fascia sutures',
  'facelift vectorization',
  'natural facelift result',
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Fixation Vectors"
  description="Vertical vectorization in Endomidface. Fixation points on deep temporal fascia, suture materials."
  keywords={keywords}
  lang="en"
>
  <section class="py-32 bg-primary-900">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-[10px] font-medium text-accent-600 uppercase tracking-[0.2em] mb-4">
        Fixation & Support
      </p><h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-serif text-white mb-6">Fixation Vectors</h1><p
        class="text-xl text-primary-300 max-w-2xl mx-auto"
      >
        The vertical vector is the Endomidface signature. Understand fixation logic and how to
        ensure lasting results.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="py-20 bg-ivory">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4">
      <p class="text-warmGray text-lg drop-cap">
        Unlike traditional facelift techniques that pull tissues backward (posterior vector),
        Endomidface promotes vertical elevation — upward, against gravity. This technical decision
        has two fundamental consequences: we don't need to release the strongest lateral ligaments
        (especially the zygomatic), and we reduce manipulation of dangerous zones.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif text-primary-900 mb-12 text-center">Fixation Points</h2><div
        class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8"
      >
        <div class="p-8 bg-ivory">
          <span class="text-5xl font-serif text-accent-600/30 block mb-4">01</span><h3
            class="font-serif text-primary-900 mb-3"
          >
            Lateral Fixation
          </h3><p class="text-warmGray mb-4">
            Sutures on deep temporal fascia, as posterior and superior as possible.
          </p><ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-warmGray">
            <li>→ Material: Vicryl 2-0</li><li>→ Goal: elevate mobilized SMAS flap</li><li>
              → Protection: position posterior to incision to avoid frontal nerve
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div><div class="p-8 bg-ivory">
          <span class="text-5xl font-serif text-accent-600/30 block mb-4">02</span><h3
            class="font-serif text-primary-900 mb-3"
          >
            Medial Fixation
          </h3><p class="text-warmGray mb-4">
            Muscle flap from temporalis to anchor medial portion of midface.
          </p><ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-warmGray">
            <li>→ Flap of ~0.5-1 cm of temporal muscle</li><li>
              → Allows adequate vertical traction
            </li><li>→ Essential where temporal muscle isn't directly available</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="py-20 bg-ivory">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="bg-white p-10">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-serif text-red-600 mb-4">✕ Lateral Vector (Incorrect)</h3><ul
              class="space-y-3 text-sm text-warmGray"
            >
              <li>Backward traction toward ear</li><li>"Stretched" unnatural appearance</li><li>
                Short-lasting result
              </li><li>Requires releasing strong ligaments</li>
            </ul>
          </div><div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-serif text-green-600 mb-4">✓ Vertical Vector (Correct)</h3><ul
              class="space-y-3 text-sm text-warmGray"
            >
              <li>Upward elevation against gravity</li><li>Natural "top model look" result</li><li>
                8-12 year durability
              </li><li>No need to release lateral ligaments</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="py-16 bg-primary-900">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-xl font-serif italic text-white mb-6">
        "Our intention is to pass in front of the ligaments, dissect everything in front, and
        reposition upward — not backward. That's why it's possible. That's why it's safe."
      </p><footer class="text-sm text-primary-400">— Dr. Robério Brandão</footer>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="py-8 bg-white border-t">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 flex justify-between">
      <a href="/techniques/endomidface/anatomy" class="text-sm text-accent-600">← Anatomy</a><a
        href="/techniques/endomidface/step-by-step"
        class="text-sm text-accent-600">Step by Step →</a
      >
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
